Package org.bluezoo.gumdrop.telemetry.protobuf

Class DefaultProtobufHandler

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.bluezoo.gumdrop.telemetry.protobuf.DefaultProtobufHandler
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    ProtobufHandler
    public class DefaultProtobufHandler
extends java.lang.Object
implements ProtobufHandler
    Default implementation of ProtobufHandler with no-op methods.

    Extend this class and override only the methods you need. This class also provides helper methods for interpreting raw wire values.

    Author:
    Chris Burdess

        public void handleVarint​(int fieldNumber,
                         long value)
        Description copied from interface: ProtobufHandler
        Called when a varint field is encountered.

        The value may represent: int32, int64, uint32, uint64, bool, or enum. For sint32/sint64, apply zigzag decoding: (value >>> 1) ^ -(value & 1)

        Specified by:
        handleVarint in interface ProtobufHandler
        Parameters:
        fieldNumber - the field number
        value - the raw varint value (unsigned)

      • handleBytes

        public void handleBytes​(int fieldNumber,
                        java.nio.ByteBuffer data)
        Description copied from interface: ProtobufHandler
        Called when a length-delimited field is encountered that is not a message.

        The data may represent: bytes, string (UTF-8), or packed repeated fields. The buffer is positioned at the start of the data and has exactly the field's length remaining.

        Specified by:
        handleBytes in interface ProtobufHandler
        Parameters:
        fieldNumber - the field number
        data - the field data (read-only view)

      • isMessage

        public boolean isMessage​(int fieldNumber)
        Description copied from interface: ProtobufHandler
        Returns true if the given field number represents an embedded message.

        The parser calls this to determine whether to recursively parse a length-delimited field as a message or deliver it as raw bytes.

        Specified by:
        isMessage in interface ProtobufHandler
        Parameters:
        fieldNumber - the field number
        Returns:
        true if this field is an embedded message

      • startMessage

        public void startMessage​(int fieldNumber)
        Description copied from interface: ProtobufHandler
        Called when parsing begins for an embedded message.

        The handler should push any state needed to track the nested context. All subsequent handler calls relate to fields within this message until ProtobufHandler.endMessage() is called.

        Specified by:
        startMessage in interface ProtobufHandler
        Parameters:
        fieldNumber - the field number of the message field

      • endMessage

        public void endMessage()
        Description copied from interface: ProtobufHandler
        Called when parsing completes for an embedded message.

        The handler should pop the nested context and return to the parent.

        Specified by:
        endMessage in interface ProtobufHandler
